entities.description: An estimated quantity derived from the survey, represented as a numeric value.
A specific category or label for the survey response.
The raw, unweighted frequency of responses within a particular category.
The total count of all survey responses.
The count of missing data within the survey.
A statistical measure derived from the survey data.

relationships.description: Indicates the raw count of responses for each survey category.
Each survey response category is part of the total survey responses.
The total survey count includes a certain amount of missing data.
Statistics are computed using the total survey responses.
Statistics are computed from the estimated quantity derived from the survey responses.
